### Why `CONCURRENTLY` was the only safe choice here

A standard `CREATE INDEX` on a 500M-row table would have acquired an **`AccessExclusiveLock`** for an estimated **10–15 minutes**, blocking every `INSERT`, `UPDATE`, and `DELETE` on `orders` — effectively taking down order processing site-wide.

`CREATE INDEX CONCURRENTLY` does two passes over the table while holding only a `ShareUpdateExclusiveLock`, which doesn't conflict with DML. It takes ~2–3× longer to build, but production writes continued uninterrupted throughout.

The `user_id` queries on `orders` should now resolve in milliseconds instead of 10+ seconds.
